verbose_text: The data herein demonstrates that baicalin treatment increases canonical Wnt pathway signaling in mouse skin tissues by increasing the levels of Wnt3a, Wnt5a, frizzled 7, disheveled 2, beta-catenin and LEF1, while decreasing the expression of the beta-catenin degradation complex member GSK3beta.
evidence: expression of the beta-catenin degradation complex member GSK3beta
